      \field{abstract}{This paper addresses the energy management control problem of solar power generation system by using the data-driven method. The battery-supercapacitor hybrid energy storage system is considered to smooth the power fluctuation. A new model-free control method is utilized in the stand-alone photovoltaic {DC}-microgrid to provide the power to meet the demand load, while guaranteeing the {DC} bus voltage is stable. Furthermore, the proposed data-based power management control strategy only needs I/O data. Numerical simulations with real data verify the effectiveness of the proposed method.}
